The government is condemning the violence, saying that the freight and logistics industry is vital to the economy. Labour Minister Thulas Nxesi says economic sabotage will not be tolerated. He's also appealed to employers to stop using foreign nationals as cheap labour. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The departments of Labour, Home Affairs, Transport and State Security have finally broken their silence and are condemning the ongoing truck attacks. They say they will deal decisively with the matter. READ: Ramaphosa condemns attacks on trucks Around 84 trucks have been burned or damaged since April. The government says the freight and logistics industry is vital to the economy. Labour Minister Thulas Nxesi says economic sabotage, will not be tolerated. He's also appealed to employers to stop using foreign nationals as cheap labour. For more, watch the interview above.